The location of the hotel is perfect - far enough away from all the noise of the boardwalk but close enough should you want to be within walking distance (15-20 minute walk).	Location wise, it's right on the boardwalk but not in the heart of the activity, which is good because you don't get the noise of the crowds and events.	All in all we had a comfortable stay, but if we had stayed in the original room or had to pay $75 for a quiet room, I would probably be writing a negative review.